📘 CLOSED-LOOP PATCH (CC0)
What this is
A reading extension for interaction geometry.
Base form
C ∝ O × R × S × T
Patch condition
When interaction feeds back into itself, the system may be read as:
O → R → S → T → R → S → O
What changes
Interaction is not one-pass
Output may modify origin
Coherence may emerge through return
What does not change
No domain is elevated
No variable becomes required
Replaceability remains intact
Use
Use base for simple cases
Use loop when feedback is observed
Short form
Sometimes it loops back.
